<item>
            <title>[LU-7112] Stale &quot;ops&quot; device in the &quot;AT&quot; state </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7112</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After unsuccessful lustre filesystem creation and mounting I have &lt;br/&gt;
a stale device record in &quot;AT&quot; state in MGS:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@mds1 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# lctl dl&lt;br/&gt;
..&lt;br/&gt;
40 AT osp srg-OST0000-osc-MDT0000 srg-MDT0000-mdtlov_UUID 1&lt;br/&gt;
..&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I can not create the &quot;srg&quot; lustre filesystem since the device is &quot;in use&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
It it possible to clean it online without MGS recreation?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre 2.5.2&lt;br/&gt;
CentOS 6.4&lt;br/&gt;
Kernel 2.6.32-431.17&lt;br/&gt;
Infiniband Melanox with native RedHat support</environment>
